        <updateDate>2011-11-10T16:11:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Senior Citizenship Act of 2011 - Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to: (1) exempt certain persons over the age of 75 from the U.S. history, government, and English language naturalization examination requirements; and (2) permit certain persons over the age of 65 to take such history and government examination in a language other than English.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Senior Citizenship Act of 2011</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
